President Biden has declared a major disaster in the state of Illinois and has ordered federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts following severe storm and flooding from July 25 to July 28, 2022. The declaration makes federal funding available to affected individuals in St. Clair County. Assistance includes grants for temporary housing and home repairs, low-cost loans for uninsured property losses, and other programs to help individuals and business owners recover. Federal funding is also available for hazard mitigation measures in St. Clair County. Waddy Gonzalez has been named the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Damage assessments are ongoing in other areas, and more areas and forms of assistance may be designated after assessments are completed. Residents and business owners in the designated areas can apply for assistance online or by phone. The FEMA News Desk can be contacted for further information.